On Wed, 4 Jun 2003 Shawn.Luft(-at-)Completions.Bombardier.com wrote:

> I've remarked recently that my steering is becoming quite loose.  It is

> Apparently there's a screw that I can tighten that will adjust the play for
> the wheel.

Seldom does the steering box go out of adjustment that fast, particularly
the late model worm and roller boxes.  Look elsewhere in the system for
play.  If asked to venture a wild guess, I'd check the front joint of the
drag link first.

